241
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,672
you kinda got where you needed to be.

242
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:33,674
I'll even give you a head start
on my torture.

243
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:35,426
I cannot pull off the mod look.

244
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:36,677
You can take me, too.

245
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:40,681
I couldn't live with myself knowing
you four were down there without me.

246
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:44,560
Wow! This is a toughie.

247
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:47,980
On one hand, I would love to get
some spiders in those buttholes.

248
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:51,484
On the other, there'd be billions
of buttholes going completely un-spidered.

249
00:10:52,568 --> 00:10:55,529
How about this: everyone who dies
goes to the Bad Place

250
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,948
and I get to torture all of you?

251
00:10:58,032 --> 00:10:59,200
Sounds good to us.

252
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,785
No, dummies.

253
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:03,996
That's already how it works,
except we're also tortured.

254
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,915
Look, I put forward a proposal.

255
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,792
Are you not even going to negotiate?

256
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,127
He's got a point.
The fair thing for us to do is

257
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:13,047
just keep on giving up
more and more stuff we want, unilaterally,

258
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,590
until this demon is finally happy.

259
00:11:14,673 --> 00:11:15,925
Fork this!

260
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:18,719
If we're gonna lose,
let's lose on our own terms.

261
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:23,391
Let's come up with a completely new idea
that actually makes the universe better.

262
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:26,060
Amen. At least then
we can hold our heads high.

263
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:28,145
Okay, we need to come up with

264
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:30,731
-our ideal plan in about ten minutes.
-[glass shatters]

265
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:33,234
Guys, it's all come to this.

266
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:35,986
Everything we've been through,

267
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:40,950
the multiple lives you led on Earth,
all the lives you led here,

268
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:43,619
all the ethics training and lessons,

269
00:11:43,702 --> 00:11:47,581
and journeys to the farthest corners
of the afterlife,

270
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:51,544
all happened so that
we could be here, together,

271
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:54,797
as the very best versions of ourselves,

272
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:59,343
to solve the ultimate problem
in the nick of time.

273
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,429
Cool speech. Now, it's nine minutes.

274
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:02,471
[glass shatters]

275
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:05,266
Chidi, can you do this?

276
00:12:05,349 --> 00:12:08,269
Actually, what you just said,
"the very best versions of ourselves,"

277
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:09,395
gave me an idea.

278
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,148
Ha! Turns out it was a cool speech.

279
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,107
[glass shatters]

280
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:17,027
Not in you, either.

281
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,196
-I just have one thing left to say.
-Beh-beh-beh.

282
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,782
-No--
-Not falling for that again.

283
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:22,741
[farting]

284
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:24,660
Man. She is committed.

285
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,037
That just leaves you.

286
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:29,415
Your Honor, we have an idea
we'd like to present.

287
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:31,041
Not interested, stretch.

288
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:34,587
How can we convince her of our plan
if she won't even listen?

289
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:37,673
Well, if she's not gonna stay out here,
you gotta go in there.

290
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:40,259
But that didn't really work great
last time.

291
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:41,260
Yeah, it wasn't amazing,

292
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:44,430
but she's gonna marbleize me in
two minutes, so we might as well try.

293
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:45,473
Are we all gonna be...

294
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:47,683
-you, again?
-[Janet] I don't think so.

295
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:49,935
Going through that once
changed me and all of you.

296
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:52,229
But if the Judge wasn't going to
listen to us out here,

297
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:54,690
what makes you think
she'll listen to us in there?

298
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:56,942
I know one thing
that might keep her attention.

299
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:03,866
Idiots.

300
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,162
[chuckles]

301
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:09,872
Oh, nuts!

302
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,166
How did I fall for that?

303
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:13,626
Please have a seat, Your Honor.

304
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:16,420
I already told you, I am not interested.

305
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,797
Give me one reason
why I should hear you out.

306
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:19,715
[Janet] Okay.

307
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:21,258
Here he is.

308
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:24,553
Ma'am.

309
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:31,101
You made me an Olyphant?

310
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:33,729
I think you should hear them out, Judge.
Only seems fair.

311
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:35,856
Yeah, you're probably right.

312
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,525
Well played, Janet.

313
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:41,654
I don't mind taking in the view
when the scenery is so pretty.

314
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:44,198
-Aw!
-Oh, I should call Shawn for this.

315
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:46,909
Aw, man!

316
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,411
I had just gotten all the puppies
to climb into the cannon.

317
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,538
All right.

318
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,456
Floor is yours.

319
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:54,416
So, the problem with the afterlife

320
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:57,962
is not only that it's cruel,
but that it's final.

321
00:13:58,045 --> 00:14:01,465
You get one shot on Earth, and regardless
of the context of your life,

322
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:04,802
you're placed somewhere,
usually the Bad Place, forever,

323
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:06,845
with no chance for redemption.

324
00:14:06,929 --> 00:14:10,558
My neighborhood was built to
torture humans, but it made them better.

325
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:14,436
We want to create a system
that works that way intentionally,

326
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,815
a system designed to give people
a fighting chance.

327
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:18,941
-In time--
-[Timothy] Huh?

328
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,110
-Interesting.
-[Eleanor] Oh.

329
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:23,070
Why don't you walk us through it?

330
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,322
Yeah, we're gonna, man. Just chill.

331
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:30,369
Your time on Earth won't be
a test that you either pass or fail,

332
00:14:30,452 --> 00:14:34,790
but instead a class you take,
and the test will come in the afterlife.

333
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,375
The first part stays the same.

334
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:40,254
You live your life, screw up
a bunch of stuff, like, a lot of stuff,

335
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:45,259
to the point where people are like,
"This is messed up, even for Florida."

336
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:47,970
But you can't hear them,
because you fell into the swamp

337
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:51,015
trying to spray-paint a Taco Bell logo
on a snapping turtle.

338
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:53,058
Uh, we rest our case, Your Honor.

339
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,727
-No! No, we--
-No, no, no. No, we don't.

340
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,145
We barely started.

341
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:59,857
Uh, so, when you die,
you still have a points total,

342
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:03,652
but in the new system, that number
will serve as a sort of baseline

343
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:08,324
to determine how hard or easy
your test is.

344
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:10,868
Sorry, I'm just trying
to play catch-up here.

345
00:15:11,368 --> 00:15:13,871
Who's designing these tests, exactly?

346
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:18,792
A Good Place architect and
a Bad Place architect will work together

347
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:22,588
to design a scenario to make you confront
your moral shortcomings.

348
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:27,509
Like Eleanor's selfishness, Jason's
impulsivity, Chidi's indecisiveness

349
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:29,887
and my complete inability
to carry off a mod look.

350
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,890
-That's not--
-I know I have other faults,

351
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:34,516
but that is a big one.

352
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,018
The test could be anything.

353
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:38,896
Maybe you show up and you're told
you're in the Good Place,

354
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:40,731
but you know that it's a mistake.

355
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:43,734
Maybe the test
looks just like your regular life

356
00:15:43,817 --> 00:15:46,070
or a twisted version of your life.

357
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,822
You're presented with these challenges.

358
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:54,536
You do well or badly, but at the end,
you're given a sort of evaluation.

359
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,665
Yeah, and the architects explain
what you did badly, what you did well,

360
00:15:57,748 --> 00:16:00,417
and then you get rebooted,
and do it again,

361
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:03,379
and again and again until you ace it.

362
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,297
-In the new--
-Oh, hang on.

363
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:10,344
It seems to me, if y'all get rebooted,
your memories'll be wiped out.

364
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:11,637
How are you ever gonna learn anything

365
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,472
if you're always
having to start from scratch?

366
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:15,849
-[Judge] Mmm-hmm.
-Good point, Timothy Olyphant.

367
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,518
-Tim's fine.
-'Kay, great.

368
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:20,729
In the new system,
you will retain a vague memory

369
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:23,607
of what you learned
in the evaluation sessions.

370
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:28,070
That information, what you did well
or badly, stays with you, like...

371
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,198
Like a little voice in your head,

372
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,659
helping you become
a better version of yourself.

373
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:35,786
Okay, that helps. Thank you.

374
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,706
[Chidi] So, our guess is that
with enough chances,

375
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:42,251
people will eventually make enough good
choices to qualify for the Good Place,

376
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:44,253
and maybe some never will,

377
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,672
but that's okay,
because everyone gets a fair shot.

378
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:49,466
Hold the phone.
What are my demons doing this whole time?

379
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:52,720
I have millions of lava monsters
down there who'll be out of a job.

380
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:56,348
I ask you, into whose throats
are they supposed to pour lava?

381
00:16:56,432 --> 00:16:59,768
Well, bad news is,
no more throat lava or penis flattenings.

382
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:02,396
Then, what are we doing to their penises?

383
00:17:02,479 --> 00:17:04,106
Well, largely ignoring them.

384
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,443
You guys are hearing this.
I'm not crazy, right?

385
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:08,694
No, I mean, it's a fair question.

386
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:10,529
Whose side are you on, man?

387
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:13,032
I don't have a dog in this fight,
little lady.

388
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:14,575
I'm just looking for clarity.

389
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:16,118
Shawn, you'll all still have jobs.

390
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:19,538
Bad Place architects
help design the tests.

391
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:22,124
Rank and file demons, they'll play roles,

392
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:24,460
just like they did
in my original neighborhood.

393
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,628
And remember how much fun
you had playing the Judge?

394
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:29,089
I don't know, guys.
You think this'll work?

395
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:30,966
It sort of already has.

396
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:35,971
Chidi just had 800 versions of himself
stuffed into his soul at the same time.

397
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:39,183
I mean, he's a new man.
He's way cooler now.

398
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:42,561
Uh, I liked the old version, too,
but not as much.

399
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:44,063
It's not just Chidi, Your Honor.

400
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,856
When I started
in Michael's first neighborhood,

401
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:49,109
I was nothing more than
a PalmPilot in a cool vest,

402
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:50,569
but look at me now.

403
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:53,155
I can hold four humans in my void

404
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:56,075
and conjure Timothy Olyphant
in the blink of an eye.

405
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:59,995
Getting rebooted over and over made me
a better not-a-person than I've ever been.

406
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,372
Humans should get the same opportunity.

407
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:04,458
[heartfelt music playing]

408
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:05,918
Well?

409
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:13,383
Hmm.

410
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,468
Pass!

411
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,888
[Judge] Well, guys,
I really thought you had it.

412
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:21,016
It has been a genuine pleasure, sweetie.

413
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:22,851
Oh. [chuckles]

414
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:32,694
<i>♪ Gonna erase the Earth</i>
<i>Erase the Earth ♪</i>

415
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:37,074
I hid the clicker as far away as possible,
but we are seconds away.

416
00:18:37,157 --> 00:18:38,534
I'm so sorry, guys.

417
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:39,660
Where did Shawn go?

418
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:42,079
Oh, don't bother.
He's just toying with us.

419
00:18:42,162 --> 00:18:44,706
I know. That's what gives me hope.

420
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:47,167
-[urinating]
-[Shawn chuckles]

421
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,670
Had to do it one last time
before all this goes away for good.

422
00:18:49,753 --> 00:18:53,173
-So, what are you offering me now?
-Nothing. It's over.

423
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:55,425
-That was our last idea.
-[zips pants]

424
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:56,343
Good.

425
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:58,720
Soon, all your precious humans
will be gone.

426
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,557
Yeah. It's too bad.

427
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:06,103
Well, congrats, bud. You won.
See you in a billion years.

428
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:09,940
When humans evolve again, I'll be
right back at your throat, you traitor!

429
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:12,401
[chuckles] I mean, yeah, I know.

430
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,154
That's why I said,
"See you in a billion years."

431
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:16,071
Wait.

432
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:18,490
I'm gonna do the evil speech now.

433
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:19,533
If you want.

434
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:20,617
[clears throat]

435
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:23,745
"Since the dawn of time,

436
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:26,665
good and evil have waged a furious battle,
stemming from..."

437
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:28,417
This feels stupid
if you're not gonna fight back.

438
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,545
How do you not have another plan?
You've always had another plan.

439
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:33,005
What's wrong, Shawn?

440
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,217
Okay, fine.

441
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,178
You're gonna make me admit it.

442
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:41,889
Fighting you is the most fun
I've ever had.

443
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:42,848
I mean, you know.

444
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:44,933
You corkscrew your first eyeball,
and you're like,

445
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:48,103
"Man, I can't believe
they're paying me to do this!"

446
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:52,024
But by the trillionth, it's like,
"I should have just been a teacher."

447
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:55,861
And then you go and get the warm fuzzies
about your little humans, and something...

448
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:57,613
something changed.

449
00:19:58,572 --> 00:19:59,781
I was having fun again.

450
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,036
I'm not sure I'm ready for that to end.

451
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:05,495
I know, buddy.

452
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:10,167
It's hard when things end,
but one way or the other, this is over.

453
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:13,378
The only question is, what's next?

454
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:19,760
I heard your speech at Demon-Con.
You know this system stinks.

455
00:20:19,843 --> 00:20:23,388
You wouldn't have let me try the original
experiment if things were working.

456
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:25,766
Let's try a new way.

457
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:27,351
Together.

458
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:32,231
[indistinct chatter]

459
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:33,649
[Judge] Okay, finally.

460
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:37,152
For the last time,
I, the Judge of the afterlife--

461
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:38,987
-Hang on, Your Honor.
-Argh!

462
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:40,530
Are you kidding me?

463
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:43,575
Can't a gal just end
all of humanity one time

464
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:46,078
{\an8}without everyone getting
all up on her junk?

465
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:49,373
{\an8}-What is it, man?
-Shawn has agreed to our proposal.

466
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:51,875
{\an8}-Wait, seriously?
-[Shawn] In principle, yes.

467
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:54,253
{\an8}-Still some kinks to work in.
-Out.

468
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:56,129
{\an8}Out. Sorry, old habits.

469
00:20:56,213 --> 00:20:58,465
{\an8}But I think we can find a way
to make it work.

470
00:20:58,548 --> 00:20:59,383
{\an8}[Jason] Guys, watch this!

471
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:01,593
{\an8}-[Judge] Jason!
-[all] No, no, no.

472
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:04,638
{\an8}Sorry. Jeez!

473
00:21:05,305 --> 00:21:06,640
{\an8}[Judge] Okay, well...

474
00:21:06,723 --> 00:21:12,229
{\an8}assuming we are redesigning the entire
afterlife according to this plan,

475
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:14,523
{\an8}what do we do first?

476
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:21,029
Oh, don't look at me.
I'm... I'm just the idea guy.
